The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 28 October is 799,019 (1,419.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 23 October, there were 126,061 new confirmed cases (224.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 16 October, there were 97,575 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 29% ( 28,486 extra cases).
